This is Yog vesrion 0.0.5
=========================

Yog is a dynamic programming language designed as an intermediate between Python and Ruby.

Features
--------

* Syntax like Python and Ruby
* Object Oriented
  * Class based
* Garbage Collection
* The MIT License

Requirements
------------

* CPU
  * Intel x86
* OS
  * Ubuntu Linux 8.04
  * FreeBSD 7.2
  * OpenBSD 4.5
  * Windows 2000

Documentation
-------------

Online documents are at http://neko-daisuki.ddo.jp/~SumiTomohiko/yog/0.0.1/index.html.
Offline documents are available in the ``doc/html`` directory.

Sphinx (http://sphinx.pocoo.org/) is needed to generate documents from the sources.
For generating documents, do::

  $ make doc

at the top of the source tree.

Download
--------

See

* http://github.com/SumiTomohiko/Yog/downloads

Build Instructions
------------------

See ``INSTALL``.

Issue Tracking System
---------------------

You can see the issues at http://neko-daisuki.ddo.jp/~SumiTomohiko/yog/issues/index.html.
Original data are in the ``issues`` dicretory of the source tree.

Development progress & plans
----------------------------

